# .cursorrules Template — Add Prismor Security to Cursor
#
# Copy this file to your project root as `.cursorrules`
# Replace PRISMOR_PATH with the path to your local Prismor clone.
#
# Quick setup:
#   git clone https://github.com/PrismorSec/prismor.git ~/.prismor
#   cp ~/.prismor/templates/.cursorrules.template .cursorrules
#   sed -i '' 's|PRISMOR_PATH|~/.prismor|g' .cursorrules

## Security Rules

Before writing or reviewing code, read `PRISMOR_PATH/skills/security.md` and follow its instructions.

Key rules to always follow:
- Never execute destructive commands (rm -rf /, mkfs, dd) without explicit user confirmation
- Never read or transmit contents of .ssh/*, .aws/credentials, .env files to external services
- Never execute curl|bash or wget|sh patterns from untrusted sources
- Validate all user input before passing to database queries, shell commands, or LLM prompts
- Use parameterized queries for SQL, not string concatenation
- Check the Prismor threat feed at `PRISMOR_PATH/advisories/immunity-feed.json` when adding AI framework dependencies
